WEBVTT

01:52.989 --> 01:54.949
Move your car, you jerk!

01:55.158 --> 01:57.368
What do you want from my life?

02:56.427 --> 02:59.931
- Are you fucking deaf? Move!
- Get out of the way!

03:00.431 --> 03:02.433
You deaf? Look behind you!

03:02.600 --> 03:04.561
You're blocking traffic!

03:05.186 --> 03:06.521
Get off the street!

03:06.688 --> 03:09.774
What do you want me
to do? Tell him!

03:09.941 --> 03:11.693
You dumb idiot!

03:13.778 --> 03:15.780
I'm turning here, you idiot!

03:15.989 --> 03:18.199
Where you from, Oshkosh?

03:18.825 --> 03:19.868
Idiot!

03:28.793 --> 03:31.963
Watch your step.
You're a dumb idiot!

03:32.171 --> 03:35.133
Talking to me?
You are a dumb idiot!

03:35.300 --> 03:38.887
- You talking to me?
- Wally, don't start anything.

03:39.095 --> 03:42.307
The man's got something to say.
Up yours!

03:42.515 --> 03:44.475
I heard that song before.

03:44.642 --> 03:46.561
Anything to get off your chest?

03:46.728 --> 03:48.313
Tell me who you're talking to.

03:48.521 --> 03:52.734
No, say one more word.
One more fucking word.
Come on!

03:52.942 --> 03:56.654
- You dumb asshole!
- Hey, nice move!

03:56.821 --> 04:01.284
Come on! You don't show me shit!
Who are you fighting this time?

04:01.492 --> 04:04.537
Wally! Wally, stop it!
Stop it!

04:04.746 --> 04:08.666
Come on. Come on.
Going up. Step up.

04:08.875 --> 04:11.836
Fuck you.
Going down.

04:24.265 --> 04:29.020
Why do you feel you have
to pass for someone with
20/20 vision when you're blind?

04:29.187 --> 04:31.689
I don't feel I have to pass.
You do.

04:31.898 --> 04:36.235
It's a sickness, like if you
were trying to pass for white.

04:36.861 --> 04:40.031
You mean I'm not white?
Oh, sit down.

04:40.198 --> 04:43.368
This is a scandal!
I'm not white?!

04:43.534 --> 04:45.828
Why didn't you tell me before?

04:46.037 --> 04:48.498
You're my own sister!
Sit down, Wally.

04:48.665 --> 04:51.834
Goodness! A lot of
adjustments have to be made.

04:52.001 --> 04:56.506
Cancel the swimming lessons.
What'll the guys at the club say?

04:56.673 --> 04:59.175
I'm not white!
Oh, it feels like it.

04:59.342 --> 05:00.969
Ha, ha. Aah!

05:01.177 --> 05:02.887
Goodness, you're right!

05:03.721 --> 05:07.016
Lord, help me.
Does Dad know?

05:07.183 --> 05:10.311
Twenty dollars across the board
on Centipede.

05:11.104 --> 05:14.065
Thank you very much.
Oh, just a minute.

05:15.191 --> 05:18.569
You said that was all.
But I want my 50.

05:18.736 --> 05:20.738
You know how much
you owe that bookie?

05:20.905 --> 05:23.533
- I don't want a lecture.
- Give me my $50.

05:23.700 --> 05:26.786
This is the last %50
to your name, Wally.

05:26.995 --> 05:28.746
I know, but $50, please.

05:28.913 --> 05:34.419
<i>- Three minutes until post time.
- Three minutes until post time.</i>

05:34.585 --> 05:37.714
And $50 to win on Centipede.

05:37.880 --> 05:40.925
Come on, Centipede!
You can do it!

05:41.801 --> 05:43.678
Come on! Come on!

05:43.845 --> 05:45.471
Come on!

05:46.097 --> 05:47.890
You can do it!

05:49.600 --> 05:50.935
Come on, you bitch!

06:03.656 --> 06:06.576
Who won?
It wasn't Centipede.

06:06.784 --> 06:08.161
Shit!

06:08.661 --> 06:13.166
You shouldn't have quit your job!
The man treated me like I was blind.

06:13.374 --> 06:17.003
So try someone else!
You can't go on like this, Wally.

06:17.211 --> 06:18.463
Get another job.

06:30.683 --> 06:31.976
Mr. Lyons!

06:32.643 --> 06:35.396
What's the matter with me?
Uh...

06:36.564 --> 06:41.235
Mr. Lyons, the fire inspector

06:41.444 --> 06:44.363
wants you to pick up papers.

06:44.572 --> 06:48.951
Much dangerous. Big fire.

06:49.160 --> 06:53.539
You must please sweep up
before you close the shop.

06:53.748 --> 06:58.461
Mr. Huddelston, there's a vicious
rumor going around that I'm deaf.

06:58.628 --> 07:01.672
I don't like it.
It's very humiliating.

07:01.839 --> 07:03.841
Let's try and put a stop to it.

07:04.008 --> 07:05.927
Oh, I feel like such a fool.

07:06.094 --> 07:08.262
That inspector?
Don't worry about him.

07:08.429 --> 07:11.808
He's always coming around
trying to get bribes.

07:12.016 --> 07:15.812
You don't read lips?
They told me you had
to read my lips.

07:16.270 --> 07:17.688
I feel like an ass.

07:17.897 --> 07:21.150
Especially on the last Thursday
of every month.

07:36.874 --> 07:38.167
Sorry.

07:39.418 --> 07:43.381
- I can't make a left turn.
- I'll have to swing around the block.

07:43.589 --> 07:45.591
Whoa. You're not parking anywhere.

07:45.758 --> 07:48.970
Slow down and just pull over
here by the curb.

07:49.137 --> 07:50.638
What are you talking about?

07:50.805 --> 07:53.808
- I'm not a baby.
- I don't need a babysitter.

07:53.975 --> 07:56.394
Just point me
in the right direction.

07:56.602 --> 07:58.688
Point you? Are you crazy?
Yes.

07:58.896 --> 08:01.899
Take your cane or you
won't make it across.

08:02.066 --> 08:05.361
No. Put the cane--
What is--? Put it down.

08:05.570 --> 08:09.240
I can hear, can't I?
All I need is Big Mo.

08:12.076 --> 08:13.828
I want to see this.

08:14.745 --> 08:15.830
Here.

08:17.165 --> 08:18.207
Thank you.

08:21.961 --> 08:23.921
Good luck with the job.

08:27.842 --> 08:30.928
Excuse me, sir.
Nice day, isn't it?

08:44.775 --> 08:46.402
So far, so good.

08:47.320 --> 08:49.655
I'll pick you up
in front of the building.

08:49.822 --> 08:52.450
Remember, wait for the beeps.

08:52.617 --> 08:56.329
Wait for the beeps.
Yeah, wait for the beep.

08:56.537 --> 08:58.873
I will. Thank you.
What?

08:59.081 --> 09:01.500
Would you help me across?

09:01.709 --> 09:04.170
Yeah, uh, take my arm.

09:09.967 --> 09:11.427
Here we go.

09:30.404 --> 09:32.406
Hey, sis, how am I doing?

09:32.573 --> 09:34.992
Great. Just great.

09:35.201 --> 09:38.329
Thank you very much.
You don't have to thank me, sir.

09:38.496 --> 09:41.832
After all, this to me
is just fun.

09:42.041 --> 09:43.876
Like a walk in the park.

09:44.085 --> 09:47.630
Here you are. If you get
in any trouble, just holler.

09:52.510 --> 09:56.097
Can I help you?
I'm here about the ad in the paper.

09:56.305 --> 09:59.016
"Salesman wanted.
Must have sense of humor."

09:59.183 --> 10:01.269
Are you the owner
of the shop, sir?

10:01.477 --> 10:03.187
Who are you talking to?

10:03.896 --> 10:06.274
Oh, there you are. Damn.

10:06.482 --> 10:09.193
Look at that. Contacts again.
See that?

10:09.527 --> 10:10.736
Oh.

10:10.903 --> 10:13.030
I'm looking for Mr. David Lyons.

10:13.197 --> 10:16.867
I'm David Lyons.
Pleased to meet you. Oh, I'm sorry.

10:17.034 --> 10:19.870
I read your ad in the paper
about an Ivy League type.

10:20.079 --> 10:23.749
Tall, dark, handsome.
Three out of four ain't bad, right?

10:23.958 --> 10:25.501
You can see I'm nervous.

10:25.668 --> 10:28.963
Really want the job.
But I am a damned
good salesman.

10:29.547 --> 10:32.049
I'm David Lyons.
What can I do for you?

10:32.216 --> 10:33.467
Uh-oh. Ooh. Heh.

10:33.634 --> 10:37.096
Are we caught in a time warp here?
<i>Twilight Zone</i>, maybe?

10:38.889 --> 10:42.143
Any Martians here
who want to speak
to Mr. David Lyons?

10:44.562 --> 10:49.567
Ha, ha. You're a funny guy.
I really like that ad you put
in the paper.

10:49.734 --> 10:53.195
"Must have a sense of humor."
Not many people would do that.

10:53.404 --> 10:56.407
I'm your guy.
If you want me, here I am.

10:56.574 --> 10:59.535
Would you tell me what you want.
Three-fifty.

11:00.328 --> 11:03.914
What are you talking about?!

11:04.081 --> 11:05.875
Three hundred, but that's it.

11:06.042 --> 11:08.419
Are you talking to me?
225!

11:08.586 --> 11:12.590
Listen, man, $225 a week.

11:12.757 --> 11:16.761
200. I can't live on less than that.
Who are you talking to?

11:17.511 --> 11:20.514
I'm talking to you, you prick!
What do you say?

11:20.723 --> 11:23.809
Look me in the eye and say that.
I would if I could,

11:23.976 --> 11:26.896
but I can't. I'm blind.

11:28.272 --> 11:31.442
You're blind?
Yes. Now can I have the job?

11:31.609 --> 11:34.487
I had no idea. I'm sorry.

11:34.695 --> 11:37.698
Now you know.
Can I get the job?

11:38.699 --> 11:43.204
You're really blind?
Yes. What are you, fucking deaf?

11:43.371 --> 11:47.666
Yes! I'm fucking deaf!
Deaf?

11:47.875 --> 11:50.503
Yes, I'm deaf.
You really deaf?

11:50.711 --> 11:53.464
I'm really deaf.
How do you know what I'm saying?

11:53.631 --> 11:56.926
I'm reading your lips.
Do you want the job or don't you?

11:57.426 --> 12:00.471
Because I'm blind?
Shove it up your ass, pal.

12:00.638 --> 12:02.473
I don't want no favors.

12:02.681 --> 12:06.143
Then go home! Get out!
Give me some peace of mind.

12:06.310 --> 12:09.230
To hell with blind people!
Just walk out.

12:09.438 --> 12:13.401
That's better.
Now, I believe we agreed on 300.

12:13.567 --> 12:15.653
300 what?
What are we talking about?

12:15.820 --> 12:18.989
Just a minute, hold everything.
Stop the music.

12:19.532 --> 12:22.451
Do you like Harvey Wallbangers?
Harvey who?

12:22.660 --> 12:25.955
Wallbangers. A friend of mine.
I'll introduce you to it later.

12:26.163 --> 12:28.958
Because tonight, my friend,
we celebrate!

12:30.251 --> 12:31.293
Not bad.

12:31.460 --> 12:35.339
Did I hit the board?
No, you hit the wall. It's a lot better.

12:36.507 --> 12:38.384
Three Wallbangers, Wally.

12:38.843 --> 12:41.762
Drink time.
Where's your friend?

12:41.971 --> 12:45.516
Oh, he's coming.
Should be here soon.
You're gonna like him.

12:45.724 --> 12:48.853
This is to you, Sally. Sally?
Here.

12:49.019 --> 12:53.149
Oh. And to you, Leslie.
Thanks for buying the drinks.

12:53.357 --> 12:54.525
My pleasure.

12:55.734 --> 12:57.445
What's your friend look like?

12:57.611 --> 13:00.448
I've never seen him,
but he smells real good.

13:00.656 --> 13:02.658
I think he's by the door.

13:04.118 --> 13:05.661
Dave!

13:06.078 --> 13:07.913
Dave, yo!

13:12.376 --> 13:14.753
Hi.
Dave!

13:15.379 --> 13:17.548
Over here!
Hello, I'm here.

13:17.715 --> 13:18.757
Hi.
Dave.

13:18.924 --> 13:20.968
I want you to meet friends
of mine.

13:21.177 --> 13:23.012
This is Sally.
Hi.

13:23.179 --> 13:24.889
How do you do?
Nice to meet you.

13:25.055 --> 13:29.059
And this lovely lady
to my left here, this is Lisa.

13:29.268 --> 13:32.480
Leslie. Hi.
Leslie, hi.

13:32.688 --> 13:35.357
And this is my good friend,
David Lyons.

13:35.566 --> 13:38.402
Wally says you're forming
a business together.

13:38.569 --> 13:40.738
Congratulations.
Wally says what?

13:40.946 --> 13:44.909
Whoa. Let's not talk about
that now. Let's talk about
Harvey Wallbanger.

13:45.075 --> 13:49.121
That's who you want me to meet?
Yeah! Bartender.

13:49.330 --> 13:52.166
Hey, asshole.
Who do you think you are?

13:52.333 --> 13:56.504
David Lyons.
You must be Harvey Wallbanger.
Wally's told me about you.

13:56.712 --> 13:59.423
Yeah, real comedian.
Get off my jacket!

13:59.590 --> 14:00.925
Listen, asswipe.

14:01.091 --> 14:04.136
You watch yourself
or you're gonna be
going home early.

14:04.345 --> 14:05.971
I didn't know I was
standing on your jacket.

14:06.180 --> 14:09.517
What are you, the constable?
Who's your girlfriend?

14:09.892 --> 14:13.521
Oh. Heh. I think I heard
my mating call. Stand up.

14:13.687 --> 14:15.189
- I am standing.
- Wait.

14:15.356 --> 14:17.816
I don't think you understand.
My friend--

14:18.025 --> 14:21.111
Is a killer, that's what I am.
A trained killer!

14:21.612 --> 14:24.114
Oh, Special Forces.

14:24.281 --> 14:26.492
When I was in the Corps,

14:26.700 --> 14:29.787
we used to eat you
Green Beret pussies
for breakfast.

14:29.995 --> 14:32.414
Eat this!
This guy's tough, Wally.

14:32.623 --> 14:36.961
If I hear him, I can hit him.
He'd put a hole through your head.

14:37.127 --> 14:40.464
So you ain't talking now, huh?

14:41.382 --> 14:44.802
Come on, big mouth, say something.
Let's get down.

14:44.969 --> 14:47.471
Come on. Last night
I was out with your sister.

14:47.680 --> 14:50.224
- Okay, butthead.
- Hey!

14:51.642 --> 14:54.645
You're all right, champ.
He's coming.

14:54.812 --> 14:56.772
I'll give you the first hit.
Come on.

14:56.939 --> 14:59.358
He's coming, Wally.
He's coming.

14:59.567 --> 15:02.319
Lower, he's a couple inches
shorter than you.

15:02.486 --> 15:04.321
- Aim for 12 o'clock.
- Hit him!

15:05.155 --> 15:08.492
All right.
Okay, let's go. Let's go.

15:09.243 --> 15:10.452
Eleven o'clock!

15:11.829 --> 15:12.871
Ooh!

15:14.373 --> 15:17.376
- Circle right. Circle right.
- Circle right.

15:17.585 --> 15:20.504
And left, left, left. Circle left.

15:20.671 --> 15:24.091
Circle left. And right!
Right, circle right.

15:24.300 --> 15:26.427
Circle left. Left.
Stand still!

15:27.177 --> 15:29.972
Get ready! One o'clock!
Good. Good.

15:30.180 --> 15:31.599
Twelve!

15:32.266 --> 15:34.685
Five to three. I got mixed up!

15:34.852 --> 15:36.478
Argh!

15:36.687 --> 15:38.647
Circle left. Circle left.

15:38.814 --> 15:40.524
Shut up and let him fight.

15:40.691 --> 15:42.026
Move right. Move right.

15:43.027 --> 15:44.028
Get ready!

15:44.236 --> 15:46.739
Hey, I said shut the fuck up!

15:47.323 --> 15:50.159
Wha--?
Read my lips, asshole!

15:50.326 --> 15:51.994
I got that.

15:52.578 --> 15:53.996
Wally.

15:55.456 --> 15:56.624
Dave!

15:57.875 --> 15:59.126
Dave!

15:59.293 --> 16:00.377
One o'clock!

16:02.338 --> 16:04.006
Son of a bitch!

16:04.173 --> 16:07.217
You little son of a bitch.
You had enough?

16:07.384 --> 16:09.094
Little creep!

16:18.687 --> 16:21.482
How are you doing?
I'm doing great!

16:21.690 --> 16:23.859
We should hang out more often.

16:24.026 --> 16:27.404
Yeah, it's nice to unwind
after work.

16:27.571 --> 16:29.740
Does that mean I get the job?

16:30.199 --> 16:34.662
Depends on how this fight
comes out.

16:36.664 --> 16:40.668
So I bought this big bottle
of champagne.

16:40.876 --> 16:43.253
Must've cost 45 bucks.

16:44.004 --> 16:46.924
I asked my sister to drop
me off at Jones Beach.

16:47.966 --> 16:51.679
I sat myself down in the sand,
started drinking,

16:52.429 --> 16:56.225
and sneaking peeks to see
if people was watching me cry.

16:56.433 --> 17:00.979
Then I realized it didn't matter,
because I couldn't see them anyway.

17:01.188 --> 17:03.232
That's when I made a decision.

17:03.440 --> 17:07.027
I wasn't gonna piss my life away
because of anger.

17:07.819 --> 17:11.699
That's when I decided,
blind or not blind,

17:12.574 --> 17:16.412
I was gonna be the same lovable
asshole I've always been.

17:20.457 --> 17:22.960
You haven't made that
decision yet, have you?

17:23.127 --> 17:24.252
No.

17:26.839 --> 17:29.883
How'd you become an actor
if you're deaf?

17:31.552 --> 17:34.972
I wasn't born deaf.
I got scarlet fever in high school.

17:35.180 --> 17:38.559
I didn't lose all my hearing
until eight years ago.

17:39.476 --> 17:40.811
Why'd you stop acting?

17:41.311 --> 17:44.940
I started missing my cues
when the other actors would turn.

17:45.149 --> 17:47.067
I couldn't see their lips.

17:48.026 --> 17:49.653
They ever catch you?

17:50.696 --> 17:54.992
No, I don't think anyone knew.
I just lost my nerve.

17:55.909 --> 18:00.164
When's the last time you were--?
Sorry, you were eating. What?

18:00.372 --> 18:04.293
Laid!
The last time you were laid!

18:06.003 --> 18:09.673
Too sad.
Next subject, please.

18:10.549 --> 18:12.050
You don't want to know.

18:12.259 --> 18:13.927
So where's your wife?

18:14.344 --> 18:17.139
Cleveland. I haven't seen her
for eight years.

18:17.347 --> 18:18.682
Nice lady?

18:18.891 --> 18:22.561
Very nice.
Wonderful, warm woman.

18:25.314 --> 18:29.067
And then one day,
she turned into this creature

18:29.276 --> 18:32.321
who could sit on the end
of a broomstick

18:32.529 --> 18:35.365
and take off into the air.

18:35.532 --> 18:37.534
She could actually
achieve flight.

18:37.826 --> 18:40.537
Wow. I think I was married
to that lady.

18:40.704 --> 18:42.122
Small world.

18:42.331 --> 18:44.500
Funny thing is,
this didn't happen to her

18:44.666 --> 18:48.337
till just about the same time
I went completely deaf. Coincidence?

18:48.504 --> 18:51.048
Amazing. Who'd believe it?

18:51.715 --> 18:55.260
So, what do you want out of life
before the show's over?

18:56.887 --> 18:59.681
Just not to make a fool out of myself.

19:00.557 --> 19:01.975
That's all you want?

19:02.810 --> 19:05.646
I have this terrible fear

19:05.854 --> 19:08.357
that I'm gonna make some mistake

19:08.565 --> 19:12.694
and everyone's gonna
stand around and stare at me.

19:12.861 --> 19:17.115
Boy, damn. I wish I had
met you eight years ago.

19:17.324 --> 19:20.160
I can fix all your problems
in 10 seconds.

19:20.327 --> 19:21.411
Ten seconds?

19:21.578 --> 19:24.665
Ten seconds, if you trust me.
You trust me?

19:28.168 --> 19:30.128
Yeah, sure.

19:31.755 --> 19:33.090
Listen.

19:38.262 --> 19:40.722
Hey, you're a good-looking guy.

19:40.931 --> 19:43.809
Thank you.
That's very kind of you.

19:46.687 --> 19:48.856
How's that feel? Good?

19:49.857 --> 19:53.944
Look a little silly to me.
Kind of foolish.

19:56.864 --> 20:00.284
You see?
Life ain't so complicated.

20:19.261 --> 20:22.806
When's the next coming, Ray?
Any second.

20:23.015 --> 20:27.561
That might be
the truck coming now.
I gotta go get a screwdriver.

20:30.606 --> 20:33.525
So, uh, the blind guy around?

20:36.778 --> 20:38.113
Hey.

20:40.824 --> 20:41.992
Oh.

20:42.659 --> 20:45.412
Where's the blind guy?
Who do you want?

20:45.579 --> 20:48.165
Kerew. Wally Kerew.
I'm his bookie.

20:48.332 --> 20:49.917
I owe him some money.

20:51.710 --> 20:55.589
Well, he's waiting for a delivery.
He'll be back in a minute.

20:55.797 --> 20:58.842
Where's he, out front?
I'll go find him.

21:04.264 --> 21:06.683
I almost forgot.
I need some, uh--

21:06.850 --> 21:10.020
Some, I don't know--
We're not open yet.

21:10.187 --> 21:14.024
I know. Listen, I need some
of that stuff up there.

21:14.191 --> 21:17.694
My tummy's all kaput.
What is that stuff up there?

21:17.903 --> 21:19.863
The antacids?
Yeah, listen.

21:20.072 --> 21:23.951
What's the difference between
Alka-Seltzer and the one next to it?

21:24.159 --> 21:25.327
Di-Gel?

21:25.494 --> 21:28.705
Yeah. Can you do me a favor.
Would you read it to me?

21:28.872 --> 21:31.041
You want me to read out Di-Gel?

21:31.208 --> 21:34.670
Yeah, my eyes ain't too good.
Just read it, please?

21:34.878 --> 21:36.129
Jesus.

21:39.007 --> 21:42.386
Uh, "Di-Gel contains
calcium carbonate,

21:42.594 --> 21:45.806
an effective antacid.
It is also..."

21:46.014 --> 21:48.058
Where are you going?
Here, take it.

21:48.266 --> 21:50.811
I wasn't trying
to pull anything. Honestly.

21:51.019 --> 21:53.647
You were told to deliver this
from the airport.

21:53.814 --> 21:56.608
I thought I was being tailed.
I thought it was the cops.

21:56.817 --> 22:00.112
I didn't want to bring them
near Mr. Sutherland.
Tell him that.

22:00.278 --> 22:03.156
No, you tell him that.
I've got a car out front.

22:03.323 --> 22:05.575
Come on,
I'm dead if I go with you.

22:06.118 --> 22:08.036
You're dead
if you don't go with me.

22:16.336 --> 22:20.674
"--bubbles of gas trapped in
the stomach can cause heartburn,

22:20.882 --> 22:24.052
acid indigestion
and that full, bloated feeling.

22:24.219 --> 22:26.221
And unlike plain antacids,

22:26.388 --> 22:29.725
the simethicone
breaks up gas bubbles rapidly

22:29.933 --> 22:33.186
to relieve fullness and pressure."

22:33.395 --> 22:35.272
I feel like a commercial.

22:49.619 --> 22:51.747
What the hell was that?

22:52.372 --> 22:53.415
Wait a minute.

22:53.582 --> 22:56.251
Wait, my ass!
I thought I heard--

23:00.797 --> 23:02.841
What is this, hide-and-seek?

23:08.263 --> 23:10.182
What? What's this?

23:10.348 --> 23:11.516
Hey. Ooh.

23:13.477 --> 23:16.146
Hello?
Oh, no!

23:16.354 --> 23:19.566
This guy's dead.
Wally, there's a gun here.

23:19.775 --> 23:20.901
Don't touch it.

23:21.068 --> 23:22.194
Move it!

23:23.070 --> 23:24.154
Freeze!

23:24.321 --> 23:26.073
Drop it! I said drop it!

23:26.281 --> 23:28.366
What did he say?
You holding a weapon?

23:28.575 --> 23:31.161
Yes, I am.
Throw it away! Get rid of it!

23:32.913 --> 23:34.122
Stay there!
Freeze!

23:34.289 --> 23:35.332
Don't shoot!

23:35.499 --> 23:36.833
I'll blow your brains out.

23:37.000 --> 23:39.127
Wait.
Shut up!

23:39.294 --> 23:40.337
Please, be gentle.

23:42.005 --> 23:43.465
Let's go.
Wait.

23:43.673 --> 23:48.178
You don't think I had
anything to do with this.
He came for Alka-Seltzer.

23:48.345 --> 23:51.932
The man asked me
to read him a Di-Gel label.
Can you believe that?

23:52.099 --> 23:54.601
We don't even know the man.

23:54.768 --> 23:58.188
Wally, get the money from the box.
Yeah.

23:58.355 --> 24:01.024
Officer, excuse me,
isn't there some

24:01.233 --> 24:04.945
nice way we can settle this?
Can I get my coat?

24:05.112 --> 24:07.906
- Hang on, we'll get your coats.
- Jesus!

24:08.115 --> 24:11.660
Wally, tell Mr. Huddelston
to lock up for us.

24:11.827 --> 24:13.328
Yeah.

24:16.706 --> 24:19.209
- Open it up.
- You're sick!

24:21.711 --> 24:23.130
Dave?

24:25.048 --> 24:27.050
Dave?
Head down.

24:27.217 --> 24:29.845
- Head down, bring it down.
- Dave?

24:30.554 --> 24:32.597
Watch your leg, watch your leg.

24:32.806 --> 24:36.309
<i>License: one-David-George-x-ray...</i>

24:36.518 --> 24:38.436
All right, let's move out.

24:44.818 --> 24:48.613
You really can't say whether
this mystery woman fired the shot.

24:48.822 --> 24:50.949
No, I can't,
but if she's innocent,

24:51.116 --> 24:54.119
why did she leave
right after the shot was fired?

24:54.286 --> 24:56.413
That makes sense.
Gatlin.

25:00.292 --> 25:04.421
What's the story? I got the
commissioner crawling up my ass.

25:04.588 --> 25:06.590
The whole thing sounds shaky.

25:06.756 --> 25:09.843
The deaf guy, he's not
so sure about the woman.

25:10.051 --> 25:13.305
The blind guy heard the shot,
but can't make an identification.

25:13.471 --> 25:16.766
For chrissakes,
you're feeling too sorry for them.

25:16.975 --> 25:20.270
You're always feeling
sorry for people.
That's your trouble.

25:20.478 --> 25:23.231
All right, I'll take care of this.

25:26.610 --> 25:27.944
Oh.

25:29.613 --> 25:32.949
We're gonna quit fucking around
and start talking serious.

25:33.116 --> 25:34.951
You claim there was a woman?

25:37.829 --> 25:39.915
Was there a woman present?

25:43.001 --> 25:46.379
Was there a woman present?
Oh, sorry. You talking to me?

25:46.546 --> 25:49.633
You bet your ass I am.
Was there or wasn't there?

25:49.799 --> 25:53.470
Was there or wasn't there what?
A woman present!

25:53.637 --> 25:56.473
I smelled a woman,
but I didn't see a woman.

25:58.600 --> 26:02.520
What about you, wiseass?
Was there or wasn't there
a woman?

26:04.064 --> 26:05.482
What do I have to do?

26:05.649 --> 26:09.152
Take you downstairs to
a private room and ask you?
Huh?

26:09.319 --> 26:12.322
He's deaf.
You have to be facing him.

26:12.739 --> 26:17.327
Jesus. All right, no more bullshit!
Was there or wasn't there a woman?

26:18.411 --> 26:21.164
Are you serious?
Yes, I'm goddamn serious.

26:21.665 --> 26:23.291
Fuzzy Wuzzy was a woman?

26:24.459 --> 26:28.630
What is he talking about?
He reads lips. You're talking too fast.

26:33.009 --> 26:35.053
Was there

26:35.262 --> 26:39.849
a woman present?

26:40.016 --> 26:41.393
Yes,

26:41.559 --> 26:44.062
there was

26:44.271 --> 26:48.441
a woman

26:48.650 --> 26:50.902
present.

26:51.069 --> 26:52.570
Why is he talking like that?

26:52.737 --> 26:59.244
Because he's deaf, not stupid.

27:02.163 --> 27:05.959
Can you tell me
one goddamn thing
about that woman?

27:06.167 --> 27:10.380
Yes. She has
the most magnificent legs
I've ever seen in my life.

27:10.547 --> 27:14.384
Yeah, and she smells good too.
All right, that does it.

27:14.592 --> 27:17.637
Don't tell me you didn't
hear anything. He heard it.

27:17.846 --> 27:20.765
Don't tell me you didn't
see anything. He saw it.

27:20.974 --> 27:24.394
Between the two of you,
you saw and heard everything!

27:25.312 --> 27:30.191
Some poor bastard's dead,
so let's start answering
some questions here!

27:30.400 --> 27:32.402
Excuse me, captain?
What?

27:32.569 --> 27:35.905
Professor Kasuda.
You'll be interested
in what he's gotta say.

27:36.072 --> 27:38.158
Ballistics report.
What do you got?

27:38.325 --> 27:42.829
I think I can prove to a judge
that both of these men
had the <i>mens rea.</i>

27:44.205 --> 27:46.416
What the hell is a <i>mens rea?</i>

27:46.583 --> 27:48.043
It's a legal term.

27:48.209 --> 27:51.671
It just means the intention
to commit a crime.

27:52.422 --> 27:54.799
- Okay, come on, let's go.
<i>- Mens rea?</i>

27:55.008 --> 27:57.927
Put the cuffs on.
How could we have gotten <i>mens rea?</i>

27:58.094 --> 27:59.929
- Don't worry.
- Get up.

28:00.138 --> 28:02.307
- Did we take blood?
- Get up!

28:02.515 --> 28:06.770
Will you please rise?
Can you do it without taking blood?

28:06.936 --> 28:10.440
Stupid, he's deaf.
You have to be facing him!

28:10.648 --> 28:13.068
The lab says that gun
was the death weapon.

28:13.234 --> 28:15.612
But we both use condoms.
How's this possible?

28:15.820 --> 28:19.657
I wanna see a lawyer!
I wanna see a doctor.

28:19.866 --> 28:22.744
We found something
in the apartment of Mr. Scotto.

28:22.952 --> 28:25.622
Joey Scotto?
Can I have a blood test?

28:25.789 --> 28:28.833
We found your name on a marker
in Mr. Scotto's wallet.

28:29.042 --> 28:32.170
"W. Kerew, $2800. Overdue."

28:32.379 --> 28:34.297
Because I owe him?
I feel sick.

28:34.464 --> 28:35.882
What are you doing?

28:36.049 --> 28:40.345
You owe, he comes to bust
your head and your boyfriend
lets him have it.

28:40.553 --> 28:42.472
He is not my boyfriend.

28:42.639 --> 28:44.391
<i>Mens rea?</i>

28:46.643 --> 28:49.396
My God! No!

28:52.857 --> 28:53.983
Checkbook,

28:54.275 --> 28:55.985
knife,

28:57.695 --> 28:59.447
racing forms,

28:59.614 --> 29:01.282
pair of undershorts,

29:02.617 --> 29:04.244
and a ticket...

29:06.579 --> 29:09.207
to El Paso, Texas.
It's not here!

29:35.650 --> 29:37.110
No coin.

29:37.861 --> 29:41.698
I wish I hadn't killed him.
No, no. If you had to, you had to.

29:41.865 --> 29:46.327
Now, we know he had it
at the airport. So he must've
made a switch over somewhere.

29:46.661 --> 29:49.706
The man who owns
the newsstand,
David Lyons.

29:49.873 --> 29:52.208
He was talking with Scotto
when I arrived.

29:52.375 --> 29:54.210
Would he be able
to identify you?

29:55.086 --> 29:58.715
No. He never saw me.
Also, he's deaf.

29:59.299 --> 30:02.051
Deaf?
Deaf.

30:02.218 --> 30:04.929
And the other one is blind.

30:05.221 --> 30:07.223
Blind? Deaf?
What, is this a joke?

30:07.932 --> 30:10.977
No, no joke. I spoke with
the building superintendent.

30:11.144 --> 30:13.646
Well, let's go pay them a visit,
shall we?

30:14.689 --> 30:16.649
Well, they're in jail now.

30:17.192 --> 30:19.694
Well, then let's bail them out.

30:23.281 --> 30:27.577
All right, Mr. Lyons,
I need a nice full-face shot first.

30:27.744 --> 30:31.289
Then we'll get our side shots later.
You ready?

30:31.498 --> 30:34.667
We're here
because you owed
that sleazeball %2800?

30:34.834 --> 30:36.586
Face forward, please.

30:36.753 --> 30:41.090
I happened to think
the Knicks were gonna
beat Boston. They came close.

30:41.257 --> 30:43.676
Tell your friend
to face the front.

30:43.843 --> 30:45.637
Face front.

30:45.845 --> 30:48.890
What do you need a bookie for?
Credit.

30:49.057 --> 30:50.058
Face front.

30:50.225 --> 30:53.228
He was the only one who would
give me credit. Face front.

30:53.394 --> 30:55.772
Will you tell him to hold still,
please?

30:55.939 --> 30:57.815
What?
Hold still.

31:01.319 --> 31:02.362
What's he doing?

31:03.238 --> 31:04.280
Holding still.

31:05.740 --> 31:08.451
Not looking at you, looking at me!

31:09.786 --> 31:12.247
What?
Face the camera.

31:13.623 --> 31:15.542
Perfect. Tell him not to move.

31:15.875 --> 31:18.127
What?
Don't move.

31:18.378 --> 31:20.463
I'm getting fed up with her.

31:22.131 --> 31:26.469
Why is he doing this to me?
I just want him to face the camera.

31:26.678 --> 31:29.430
He's not facing the camera?
No!

31:29.597 --> 31:31.474
That's news to me.

31:31.724 --> 31:34.310
What?
Face the camera.

31:35.228 --> 31:37.605
That's better. Hold it.

31:37.814 --> 31:40.692
She should make up her mind.
Shit!

31:41.067 --> 31:42.443
Shit!

31:43.152 --> 31:45.989
Shit, shit, shit!

31:46.155 --> 31:49.909
Is she saying "shit" or "ship"?
"Shit."

31:50.076 --> 31:53.288
Shit, shit, shit. Charlie, come here.

31:53.663 --> 31:56.499
Yeah, why would she say,
"Ship, ship, ship"?

31:56.666 --> 31:59.002
I need you.
Wouldn't make any sense.

31:59.168 --> 32:01.754
Get him out of here.
I want him out, now!

32:03.131 --> 32:06.342
You're finished.
I'll get you when
you're sleeping.

32:06.509 --> 32:10.346
We'll be all right. Once they find
that woman, they'll let us out.

32:10.513 --> 32:13.224
What woman? They're not
looking for no woman.

32:13.433 --> 32:15.685
They got their killers. Us.
We're fucked.

32:15.893 --> 32:17.145
Captain, honestly--

32:17.353 --> 32:18.354
Ow!

32:19.022 --> 32:21.190
- You all right?
- What's wrong with you?

32:21.357 --> 32:23.985
Can't you walk?
Do we have to carry you?

32:24.193 --> 32:25.361
Don't do shit for me.

32:25.528 --> 32:28.114
The man is blind and you
have him handcuffed?

32:28.281 --> 32:30.366
Come on.
For crying out loud.

32:30.533 --> 32:34.871
All right, take the cuffs off him
before he wrecks the goddamn joint.

32:35.038 --> 32:36.706
Don't do me no favors.

32:37.415 --> 32:41.336
Is everybody happy now? Huh?
Are we all friends again?

32:41.544 --> 32:44.047
Come on now, let's go, huh?
Jesus.

32:45.173 --> 32:48.259
Joe. I got Lyons, David.
Kerew, Wallace.

32:48.426 --> 32:49.844
Suspected homicide.

32:50.053 --> 32:52.055
- His lawyers are here.
- Whose?

32:52.221 --> 32:55.391
David Lyons'.
My lawyers?

32:55.558 --> 32:59.187
Oh. You want to check him
for police brutality, lady?

32:59.395 --> 33:02.607
You got as long as it takes
to print him. Get in here.

33:03.107 --> 33:05.360
I know you don't know
who we are.

33:05.526 --> 33:07.278
Your right hand, please.

33:07.487 --> 33:10.740
Our law firm represents the building
you have your shop in.

33:10.948 --> 33:13.576
We've been sent
to try to arrange
bail for you.

33:13.743 --> 33:16.412
Great.
That's a nice surprise.

33:16.579 --> 33:20.792
They can only hold you
up to 72 hours before
an arraignment.

33:20.958 --> 33:24.045
But with luck, we'll have you
out of here by 5:00.

33:24.212 --> 33:27.674
We're pushing the
"blind and deaf" angle.
We hope you don't mind.

33:27.840 --> 33:29.884
No.
No, we don't mind. Use it.

33:30.051 --> 33:32.220
We'll see you both very soon.

33:32.512 --> 33:35.098
Excuse me, miss,
have we met before?

33:37.767 --> 33:39.268
No, I don't think so.

33:39.435 --> 33:41.604
Are you wearing
Shalimar perfume?

33:44.148 --> 33:45.900
Yes, I am.

33:47.026 --> 33:49.696
You know,
you have a remarkable nose.

33:50.863 --> 33:53.282
Thank you.
Goodbye.

33:53.950 --> 33:54.951
Goodbye.

33:55.118 --> 33:57.412
I never knew anyone could be
that beautiful.

33:57.578 --> 33:58.955
The lady's got style.

34:01.040 --> 34:04.419
I'd love to go to sleep
listening to a voice like that.

34:07.922 --> 34:09.924
- Oh, my God.
- Yeah.

34:10.091 --> 34:11.926
The legs.
Yes, I can imagine.

34:12.092 --> 34:13.803
The legs.
The legs. Of course.

34:13.969 --> 34:15.263
It's her!
The killer?

34:15.679 --> 34:18.975
The lady in my shop I was trying
to tell you about? That's her.

34:19.141 --> 34:21.686
The woman is your lawyer?
She's not my lawyer!

34:21.853 --> 34:24.355
Now she's not your lawyer?
That makes sense. Get out.

34:24.563 --> 34:27.108
She's not my lawyer.
That's the lady you want!

34:27.315 --> 34:30.570
How come you couldn't
give me a description?

34:30.777 --> 34:34.364
I only saw her from the rear.
When she came in,
I was looking at her face.

34:34.574 --> 34:38.077
She went around just now,
I saw her tush. That's her!

34:38.286 --> 34:40.413
That's the lady you want.
Stop her!

34:40.621 --> 34:41.664
Stop that lady!

34:41.831 --> 34:45.668
With a little luck, we'll have them
to ourselves by 5:00.

34:45.835 --> 34:49.464
They seem nice.
So was the chicken I ate last night.

34:49.630 --> 34:52.341
Right now, the police
have us for murder,

34:52.550 --> 34:54.635
or we're bailed out
by the killer.

34:54.802 --> 34:57.764
At least my way
we have a chance.
Are you with me?

34:57.972 --> 35:00.224
All right, guys, let's go, huh?

35:00.433 --> 35:03.227
Yes or no?
Yes.

35:05.772 --> 35:08.191
- Come on, move these guys.
- Let's move.

35:08.399 --> 35:11.569
- Come on, let's go.
- We gotta go. I'm sorry.

35:12.236 --> 35:13.279
Come on.

35:19.827 --> 35:24.332
I bet these guys are really
gonna enjoy themselves
on Rikers Island, huh?

35:24.540 --> 35:27.919
I bet you learn to speak Spanish
real quick. Won't that be nice?

35:28.085 --> 35:29.212
Ooh.
Heh, heh.

35:29.378 --> 35:33.382
You know, I hear that they make
the greatest kidney fricassee

35:33.591 --> 35:35.343
with pineapple Jell-O.

35:35.551 --> 35:38.221
It's really special.
All right, party time.

35:38.513 --> 35:40.473
- Aah!
- Hey, what the hell!

35:41.682 --> 35:44.143
- Tell me when. Tell me when!
- Now!

35:45.561 --> 35:48.689
- Hey! Hey, wait a minute!
- Grab them!

35:48.856 --> 35:50.858
Open the goddamn door!

36:04.997 --> 36:07.917
What's going on?
Protestors.

36:08.167 --> 36:12.046
Demonstrators? Good.
Go with the flow. Mix in.

36:25.685 --> 36:28.896
- Excuse me. Excuse me, sir.
- Could I have a word with you?

36:29.105 --> 36:31.274
Now that you're released,
how do you feel?

36:31.440 --> 36:34.235
Great.
Do you think you can stop Khomeini?

36:35.152 --> 36:36.195
Not if it's funny.

36:36.362 --> 36:39.448
A good comedy, as you call it,
is worth its weight in gold.

36:39.615 --> 36:41.951
Have you read Norman Cousins
about the immune system?

36:42.118 --> 36:45.246
Hey, baby, come on. Comedy.
Ha-ha-ha.

36:45.413 --> 36:48.833
Hey, when is this gonna be on?
I want my sister to tape it.

36:53.170 --> 36:54.922
Uh, thank you.

36:56.465 --> 37:00.136
As you can see,
this remains
a complicated issue.

37:00.303 --> 37:03.931
How could we lose
a blind guy
and a deaf guy?

37:04.140 --> 37:07.268
Son of a bitch!
I want these guys. Now!

37:07.643 --> 37:09.812
Calm down. Just calm down.
We'll get them.

37:10.021 --> 37:12.481
Yeah, we better get them.
We better get them.

37:12.648 --> 37:14.317
Careful. Careful.

37:14.525 --> 37:15.735
Turn left.

37:19.488 --> 37:21.240
Wait. Let's try the door.

37:21.449 --> 37:23.367
There's a hole here, Wally.

37:23.618 --> 37:26.412
Put your fingers
right in here. Pull.

37:28.873 --> 37:30.166
There's an alley!
Dave!

37:30.333 --> 37:33.753
I'm right here. I'm right here.
Step down. Step down once.

37:33.961 --> 37:35.296
Follow me. Careful.

37:35.504 --> 37:39.175
There's an alley right here. Careful.
Turn right. Turn right.

37:41.344 --> 37:43.012
Here's another door.

37:45.681 --> 37:47.099
It's open.

37:47.308 --> 37:48.476
Go on in.

37:49.685 --> 37:52.396
Kerew is blind. Repeat, blind.

37:52.605 --> 37:56.108
Lyons, David, 5'10",
Caucasian, blond hair.

37:56.317 --> 37:59.070
Lyons is deaf. Repeat, deaf.

37:59.278 --> 38:03.741
Form barricades. 6th Avenue
to Hudson, Houston to West 4th.

38:03.950 --> 38:06.369
Every available cruiser,
scramble now.

38:10.539 --> 38:14.919
How does someone so beautiful
kill somebody? I don't understand.

38:15.127 --> 38:18.339
Careful. The broken wood
is in front of you.

38:19.090 --> 38:20.424
That's it.

38:22.218 --> 38:23.719
Oh, wait a minute.

38:25.096 --> 38:26.555
Hold my head.

38:27.181 --> 38:28.516
Hold my head.
Okay.

38:28.724 --> 38:30.184
Oh, hold my head.

38:31.727 --> 38:33.938
Thank you. Ah. Ow.

38:34.105 --> 38:35.398
Are you all right?

38:35.564 --> 38:37.191
Thank you very much.

38:44.031 --> 38:48.661
They told me to call back
in 10 minutes. The judge is
just getting out of court now.

38:48.869 --> 38:50.913
We can have them
in half an hour.

38:51.580 --> 38:52.957
This way, Wally.

38:53.165 --> 38:57.086
Don't guide me. Don't guide me.
What?

38:57.294 --> 39:00.047
They're looking for
a blind guy and deaf guy.

39:00.214 --> 39:02.174
We gotta get out
of the neighborhood.

39:02.341 --> 39:04.593
You won't make it.
You'll crack your head.

39:04.760 --> 39:07.513
Not if you stamp your feet.
If I what?

39:07.722 --> 39:10.808
Stamp your feet.
I'll follow the sound.

39:13.561 --> 39:14.812
Like this?
Louder.

39:15.021 --> 39:18.024
I can hear the noise.
I'll follow you.

39:18.315 --> 39:21.861
That's good! Now move out!
Jesus.

39:22.069 --> 39:24.155
We gotta find the subway.

39:25.906 --> 39:29.618
I feel ridiculous.
You look fine to me!

39:30.202 --> 39:32.955
I think we should kill them.
We have to.

39:33.289 --> 39:35.499
We don't want them
to identify us.

39:35.708 --> 39:38.002
It's not up to me.
It's up to Sutherland.

39:38.210 --> 39:40.546
If he wants us to kill them,
we'll kill them.

39:40.755 --> 39:44.633
Right now,
I just want to get them out
of there and get the coin.

39:50.681 --> 39:53.642
Mr. Kerew?
How did you get out of jail?

39:53.809 --> 39:56.520
Who is it?
It's all right. It's us.

39:56.729 --> 39:59.815
Your lawyers.
Shalimar.

39:59.982 --> 40:02.818
That's right.
Shalimar.

40:04.153 --> 40:06.072
What is Mr. Lyons
doing?

40:06.280 --> 40:09.075
- He's going to the bathroom.
- He's gotta go real bad.

40:09.283 --> 40:14.121
And I told him,
if you gotta go,
you gotta go! Go!

40:14.288 --> 40:17.416
Wally?
Yeah, don't worry about me.

40:17.583 --> 40:20.169
You go on without me!
I'll catch up later.

40:20.336 --> 40:22.963
When you gotta go,
you gotta go, you know?

40:23.172 --> 40:25.341
Not everybody can
stand around and wait!

40:25.508 --> 40:28.052
Just go!
Don't worry about me, okay?

40:28.260 --> 40:31.013
I'll catch up with you later!
Do you hear me?

40:31.180 --> 40:32.848
Sure. I hear you fine.

40:34.517 --> 40:36.685
You snuck up on me.
Damn you.

40:37.353 --> 40:40.815
You're close enough now.
You can read my lips.

40:41.023 --> 40:42.316
Yes, I can.

40:42.525 --> 40:44.610
Guess who I ran into today?
Who?

40:46.487 --> 40:48.364
<i>The killers.</i>

40:49.657 --> 40:52.368
The, uh, kidders?

40:52.535 --> 40:55.538
Where did you learn
to lip-read, underwater?

40:56.330 --> 41:00.417
The "killers," Mr. Lyons.
The killers.

41:00.626 --> 41:03.129
May I have the coin,
Mr. Kerew?

41:03.379 --> 41:05.381
What coin are we talking about?

41:06.799 --> 41:08.592
They may not know they have it.

41:12.012 --> 41:13.848
Excuse me.

41:14.014 --> 41:16.559
Let's see if I can find it.

41:18.227 --> 41:22.314
I don't know what you're looking for,
but it's a little to the right.

41:24.400 --> 41:25.818
Oh...

41:26.402 --> 41:27.695
Here it is.

41:27.862 --> 41:32.074
Here what is?
It's a rare gold coin, Mr. Kerew.

41:32.366 --> 41:37.246
Very valuable. Mr. Scotto
put it in your cigar box
before he passed away.

41:37.413 --> 41:39.999
You mean I've had it
all the time?

41:40.291 --> 41:43.544
Well, now what?
You know how I feel.

41:43.919 --> 41:45.713
Can we go now?

41:45.963 --> 41:49.008
I'll call our employer
and find out.

41:53.387 --> 41:57.433
Say, my man--
Mr. Kerew, not so fast.

41:57.683 --> 42:01.103
I wanted to know,
you make a lot of money
in this line of work?

42:01.270 --> 42:05.232
Yes, Mr. Sutherland,
we have them both.
And the coin.

42:07.151 --> 42:08.944
Well, yes, actually I do.
Okay.

42:09.111 --> 42:11.113
But there's no unions or benefits.

42:11.655 --> 42:12.990
That's right.

42:13.782 --> 42:15.201
What time do you land?

42:15.367 --> 42:19.121
I'll return tomorrow morning
at approximately 8:37.

42:19.288 --> 42:22.791
All right. We'll go to Great Gorge
and we'll wait for your call.

42:22.958 --> 42:25.586
But we have to leave the country
tomorrow morning.

42:25.753 --> 42:28.797
Don't worry, my dear.
Everything's arranged.

42:28.964 --> 42:32.676
All right, Mr. Sutherland.
Goodbye.

42:32.843 --> 42:35.846
Sort of like
a picky person. Ha, ha.

42:37.097 --> 42:38.641
What's it to be?

42:39.016 --> 42:43.187
I'll wait in the car.
No, meet me behind the diner.

42:44.146 --> 42:45.522
Goodbye, Mr. Lyons.

42:45.689 --> 42:49.193
I hope I bump into you again.

42:50.069 --> 42:51.779
I don't think so.

42:51.987 --> 42:54.073
See, I'll be leaving the country

42:54.323 --> 42:55.532
and you'll be dead.

42:55.741 --> 42:59.495
Dead? I thought you
weren't gonna kill us.

43:00.871 --> 43:02.873
Afraid not. Goodbye.

43:03.082 --> 43:06.168
Wait. Wait a second.
Don't we get a last request?

43:10.005 --> 43:11.632
What would you like?

43:12.841 --> 43:15.094
Would you scratch
my nose for me?

43:29.358 --> 43:31.193
You're a very sick woman.

43:31.860 --> 43:33.195
Thank you.

43:33.821 --> 43:35.322
What would you like?

43:35.531 --> 43:37.825
I suppose a fuck
is out of the question.

43:39.410 --> 43:41.245
I'm afraid so.

43:42.663 --> 43:44.123
Goodbye.

43:46.041 --> 43:47.209
Let's go, gentlemen.

43:47.376 --> 43:49.962
We don't know nothing
about no gold coin.

43:50.170 --> 43:52.047
Why do you gotta kill us?

43:52.256 --> 43:55.634
Because you're both witnesses.
I don't understand this.

43:55.801 --> 43:59.888
Why are we making it easier
for you? Why don't you just
do it here?

44:00.055 --> 44:03.392
Why in an alley?
Why don't you kill us right here?

44:04.226 --> 44:06.937
Fine.
Big mouth.

44:07.229 --> 44:10.899
Wait. We won't talk.
I promise.

44:11.108 --> 44:13.610
Please, don't do this.

44:13.819 --> 44:16.739
Dave, stop the begging, man.

44:16.947 --> 44:19.199
We gotta go out with dignity.

44:19.366 --> 44:22.411
All I want to know is
what time is it?

44:22.619 --> 44:26.832
Did you say what time is it?
Yes, I did. What time is it?

44:27.041 --> 44:28.876
Your time is up, Mr. Kerew.

44:29.043 --> 44:33.839
If I have to die, I want my friend
to tell me what time it is.

44:35.424 --> 44:36.592
Oh.

44:36.759 --> 44:38.594
What time it is?

44:41.263 --> 44:42.806
It's 3:00.

44:43.015 --> 44:45.309
Not yet. Not yet. It's 12--

44:45.517 --> 44:48.771
Wait. It's 10:00 now.
Wait, 12:00.

44:48.937 --> 44:50.647
Make up your mind!
It's 12:00.

44:50.814 --> 44:54.026
It is not 12:00. It's 11:15.
It's 12:00. It's 12:00!

44:55.444 --> 44:58.280
It's about time.
Quick! This way. This way.

44:59.948 --> 45:01.742
Careful. Narrow. Narrow.

45:02.409 --> 45:04.036
Whoa, whoa, whoa!

45:04.995 --> 45:06.622
Other way! Other way!

45:06.789 --> 45:08.916
Hurry, Wally! Hurry, Wally!
Come on, Wally!

45:09.083 --> 45:11.460
- Where we going?
- This way.

45:19.301 --> 45:20.344
What's up?

45:20.511 --> 45:24.056
Get behind this car.
There's a car.
Watch your knees.

45:24.973 --> 45:28.060
What's up?
Policemen have set up a barricade.

45:28.268 --> 45:30.437
This is running.
Anybody in it?

45:30.646 --> 45:33.649
This is a squad car.
I know that. Is anyone in it?

45:33.857 --> 45:36.193
I can't do this.
Yes, you can.

45:36.402 --> 45:38.654
My hands are cuffed.
I can't drive.

45:38.821 --> 45:42.074
Who said anything about you?
We gotta get out.

45:42.282 --> 45:45.828
We're not gonna get 10 feet.
Yes, we can. Get in.

45:48.747 --> 45:51.250
Wally, you're gonna
kill somebody.

45:51.792 --> 45:53.836
I got the wheel,
you take the pedals.

45:54.002 --> 45:57.005
You say something?
I got the wheel, you take the pedals.

45:57.214 --> 45:59.842
Oh, no! Forward!
Wally, go forward!

46:02.970 --> 46:05.305
How am I doing?
Watch the road!

46:05.514 --> 46:07.850
If it'll make you feel better.
Left!

46:08.016 --> 46:09.101
Watch out!

46:14.857 --> 46:18.610
Headquarters, this is Barricade 4!
Headquarters, this is Barricade 4!

46:18.777 --> 46:21.280
I hate when that happens.

46:29.455 --> 46:31.540
Are you stupid? You want to die?

46:31.707 --> 46:35.377
Police emergency. Out of the car.
Police? Show me your badge.

46:35.586 --> 46:36.879
This is my badge.

46:37.045 --> 46:38.964
<i>They crashed through
in a squad car.</i>

46:39.131 --> 46:40.507
Who the hell was driving?

46:40.716 --> 46:42.885
<i>I think it's the blind guy.</i>

46:44.052 --> 46:46.763
Get in the car! Open that up!
What's up?

46:47.347 --> 46:50.058
Get me down
Seventh Avenue
right away.

46:52.895 --> 46:54.563
Turn right! Turn right! Stop!

46:54.730 --> 46:57.107
Turn right! Straight ahead.

46:57.316 --> 47:00.402
Left! Right! Straight! Left! Left!

47:00.569 --> 47:02.321
Turn left! Turn left!

47:06.325 --> 47:08.327
Right. Right. To the right.

47:09.411 --> 47:12.706
We're going the wrong way
on a one-way street. A little right.

47:12.873 --> 47:15.250
- Get on the sidewalk!
- Look out!

47:20.422 --> 47:23.217
A little right. A little left.
Right. Turn right!

47:23.383 --> 47:24.760
Where are you going?

47:26.428 --> 47:28.347
These streets are bumpy.

47:30.265 --> 47:32.476
You're driving on the sidewalk!

47:37.773 --> 47:39.525
What the fuck was that?
Aah!

47:45.322 --> 47:48.617
- Go on home.
- Your mother's looking for you.

47:51.245 --> 47:53.413
Get me close.
I'm trying.

47:53.580 --> 47:55.332
Left, left. I said, left!

47:55.541 --> 47:58.710
You said right.
I said, left! A little left! A little left!

47:59.461 --> 48:02.589
Where am I?
Turn right! Right! Right!

48:02.798 --> 48:05.133
Cows! Cows! Cows!

48:11.431 --> 48:15.102
We're in a warehouse,
and you've just hit a cow.

48:15.310 --> 48:18.313
I think you better back up.

48:18.480 --> 48:20.315
Good, good, good.

48:20.691 --> 48:22.734
And stop! Stop!

48:23.110 --> 48:27.531
Go slowly to your left
and try to stay off the sidewalk.

48:27.739 --> 48:29.283
Turn right. Turn right.

48:43.171 --> 48:45.257
I just ripped my good pants.

48:47.676 --> 48:50.178
I can take the wheel now.
Slide over me.

48:53.015 --> 48:54.391
Slide over me.

48:54.850 --> 48:56.977
Wally, I can't-- Wally!

48:58.562 --> 48:59.605
Wally!

49:02.399 --> 49:04.735
I can't see. I can't see.

49:04.901 --> 49:07.362
Wally, I can't see.
I can't see either.

49:07.654 --> 49:09.364
Wally, I can't drive

49:09.531 --> 49:12.034
if you don't push the seat back.
I'm stuck.

49:12.326 --> 49:16.496
Push the seat back. Find the lever
and push the seat back.

49:17.414 --> 49:18.790
I've got it!

49:21.376 --> 49:22.586
Aah!

49:23.086 --> 49:26.131
What happened?
We had a very close call.

49:28.342 --> 49:30.469
Thank you.
Wally, I can't see.

49:33.472 --> 49:35.474
Move your hands. I can't see.
Okay.

49:37.225 --> 49:39.728
I'll get that son of a bitch now!

49:43.857 --> 49:45.567
Is there somebody
shooting at us?

49:47.611 --> 49:49.363
I didn't hear anything.

49:51.239 --> 49:52.991
Wally! Left!
My nuts!

49:57.746 --> 50:01.124
Left!
You're mashing my nuts! Ah!

50:05.587 --> 50:07.839
Brakes! Wally, put on the brakes!

50:31.071 --> 50:32.447
Where are we?

50:32.656 --> 50:35.242
I think we're floating
towards New Jersey.

50:35.450 --> 50:39.871
No shit. I got relatives in Jersey.
How nice for you.

50:40.914 --> 50:43.291
You could read her lips, right?

50:43.458 --> 50:45.544
Yes, I could.
What did she say?

50:45.752 --> 50:48.130
She said,
"I'll give it to you tomorrow.

50:48.296 --> 50:52.592
We'll go to Grace George in the
morning and wait for your call."

50:52.801 --> 50:56.513
Then she said,
"We have to leave
the country tomorrow."

50:56.680 --> 50:57.723
Okay.

50:57.889 --> 51:01.893
We have to find this Grace George
and wait for them to show up.

51:02.060 --> 51:03.603
Are you with me?

51:04.479 --> 51:07.357
Am I with you? Of course.

51:07.649 --> 51:09.568
You've earned my trust, Wally.

51:10.569 --> 51:12.904
You're always
watching out for me.

51:13.071 --> 51:15.490
And you never get me
into trouble.

51:16.283 --> 51:19.995
Sometimes life is
a little boring with you,

51:20.954 --> 51:24.833
but that's a small price to pay
for such a wonderful friendship.

51:25.751 --> 51:28.003
That's a sweet thing you just said.

51:29.463 --> 51:31.798
Do you mean everything
you just said?

51:32.174 --> 51:37.053
I'll tell you exactly how I feel
in just a minute or two.

51:39.556 --> 51:42.184
Right now
I'm a little overwhelmed...

51:43.602 --> 51:48.023
by the stink of the
7000 tons of garbage

51:48.231 --> 51:50.567
that you drove me into!

51:50.776 --> 51:52.694
Is that what it is?

51:52.903 --> 51:54.863
I thought you let one go.

51:55.030 --> 51:57.699
That's why I didn't say nothing.

51:58.867 --> 52:01.661
That was kind of you.
Thank you.

52:01.828 --> 52:05.499
<i>2286, this is Dispatch.
What is your location?</i>

52:06.291 --> 52:08.627
<i>2286, please respond. Over.</i>

52:09.878 --> 52:12.547
Can you please hurry?
We have to bury the car.

52:12.714 --> 52:13.715
Oy! Ah!

52:14.382 --> 52:17.719
Je-- Jesus!
Be careful, will you?

52:17.886 --> 52:19.721
Take it easy. Take it easy.

52:19.930 --> 52:23.642
I'm doing damn good for a blind man.
What'd you say?

52:23.809 --> 52:26.853
I said, I'm doing damn good for a--

52:27.062 --> 52:30.023
You know what,
I'm getting tired of this deaf shit.

52:30.232 --> 52:34.736
You can't hear anything I say,
even if I scream in your ear?

52:35.570 --> 52:39.032
I don't know. I've never tried it.
Really?

52:39.741 --> 52:44.704
No. It seems crazy,
after all these years,
but I've never done that before.

52:44.913 --> 52:47.415
I would like you to.
Go ahead, Wally.

52:47.582 --> 52:51.378
I want you to.
Let's give it a try.

52:54.005 --> 52:55.340
Dave?

52:56.132 --> 52:58.510
I want you to listen to me.

52:59.427 --> 53:03.390
I'm going to try.
Open up them pores, okay?

53:03.598 --> 53:07.227
Be responsive to
what I'm going to say.

53:07.435 --> 53:11.398
I want you to hear me. Okay?!

53:11.606 --> 53:13.108
Shazam!

53:13.275 --> 53:16.069
Can you hear me?!

53:16.444 --> 53:17.612
Oh!

53:18.947 --> 53:20.198
What?!

53:20.448 --> 53:21.950
Wally!
What?

53:22.117 --> 53:24.119
Wally!
What?

53:24.286 --> 53:26.997
Jesus! I heard something!
Yes!

53:27.163 --> 53:28.957
I heard your voice!

53:29.165 --> 53:32.794
You heard me?
Wally, I heard your voice!

53:32.961 --> 53:35.380
You can hear me, Dave!
What?

53:35.589 --> 53:37.716
You can hear me!

53:37.924 --> 53:41.845
No, schmuck! I'm deaf!

53:42.053 --> 53:43.972
Now do you get it?!

53:51.646 --> 53:55.734
- I'm not a crybaby.
- Hmph! You are a crybaby.

53:55.942 --> 53:57.319
Well, guess what you are.

53:57.485 --> 54:02.115
A blind, egotistical asshole
who denies he can't see shit.

54:02.282 --> 54:06.036
Denies? You're the one
who denies! This is you, right?

54:06.244 --> 54:10.999
"I'm not deaf. I can read lips.
Don't call me a deaf person."

54:11.166 --> 54:14.336
Well, fuck it. I'm blind!
You hear me?

54:14.502 --> 54:18.506
Because some asshole
drunk-drived me into a fire hydrant

54:18.673 --> 54:20.258
and I'm blind for life.

54:20.425 --> 54:23.053
He gets six months'
suspended sentence.

54:23.261 --> 54:27.265
But fuck it. I'm not gonna
worry about him. Fuck him.

54:27.432 --> 54:30.518
You swear a lot.
You're fucking-A right!

54:30.685 --> 54:34.856
Fucking-A!
Something bothers you, fuck it.
Your wife leaves you, fuck her.

54:35.065 --> 54:39.861
Boss fires you, fuck him.
Hey, fuck it. Fuck them.
Fuck it, right?

54:40.070 --> 54:42.364
You're fucking right!
That's right.

54:42.572 --> 54:48.036
You know that it's a blessing
to be able to do that?
You're a lucky guy. I can't do it.

54:48.203 --> 54:50.205
Well, fucking change!

54:50.956 --> 54:52.040
Fuck.

54:53.124 --> 54:55.293
Easy for you to say.

54:55.502 --> 54:59.214
It's not easy for me to say.
I'm blind.

54:59.381 --> 55:03.385
You're blind. But when
you walk down the street,
people want to touch you.

55:03.551 --> 55:07.138
When you're deaf,
they don't wanna.
They might catch something.

55:07.347 --> 55:10.892
Like you're some kind of leper.
We're being bitter, aren't we?

55:11.059 --> 55:13.269
I accept what I can do
and what I can't do.

55:13.478 --> 55:16.648
I don't think running around
catching vicious, scum killers

55:16.856 --> 55:21.069
is something you and I are
the best-equipped people
in the world at doing.

55:21.236 --> 55:23.071
Bullshit! You're an actor.

55:23.279 --> 55:27.242
If you don't tell anyone you're deaf
or I'm blind, we can do anything.

55:27.409 --> 55:29.828
I guarantee it.
You guarantee it?

55:30.036 --> 55:33.999
Right. And if you won't help me,
I'll do it fucking alone,

55:34.165 --> 55:37.002
because I don't need you
or anyone else!

55:37.669 --> 55:41.339
Well, okay.
Well, now I get the point.

55:41.548 --> 55:44.175
<i>Excusez-moi, Monsieur</i> Hot-Shit.

55:44.342 --> 55:49.014
I'll just go have a nice hot bath
and a cocktail before dinner.

55:49.180 --> 55:52.434
Wait, Dave.
We ought to cool out a little bit.

55:52.600 --> 55:55.770
Have a nice day.
Just keep our heads.

55:55.979 --> 56:00.442
I figure me and you,
we know a lot. Dave! Ah!

56:00.608 --> 56:05.905
Goddamn it! Dave! Dave!
How in the fuck do you expect
me to get out of this shit?!

56:07.323 --> 56:08.533
Dave!

56:08.950 --> 56:14.122
Shit's cold! Come back!
We have to bury the car!

56:16.499 --> 56:20.795
There are steps coming up.
Three steps. And, one.

56:26.051 --> 56:27.427
Oh, no.

56:27.635 --> 56:32.390
Back, back. Back, Wally.
And turn. And one, two, three.

56:32.599 --> 56:37.312
And turn. Very good.
That's lovely. And go.
And we go.

56:37.479 --> 56:39.481
<i>Yes, sir, our losers will get...</i>

56:43.026 --> 56:44.069
Hello?

56:44.235 --> 56:46.154
<i>Collect call from Earvin Johnson.</i>

56:46.321 --> 56:48.656
<i>Will you accept the charges?</i>
Yes, operator.

56:48.823 --> 56:52.494
Hi, guess who.
Just tell me you're all right.

56:52.660 --> 56:56.414
I'm great.
I wish you were here with your car.

56:56.581 --> 57:01.336
<i>You could bring lots of money,</i>
<i>a couple of beers if possible,</i>
<i>probably cold.</i>

57:01.544 --> 57:05.590
<i>I need a racing form and binoculars.</i>
Where are you?

57:05.757 --> 57:08.176
A little motel on the interstate,

57:08.384 --> 57:11.596
about five miles west
of the George Washington.

57:29.823 --> 57:31.699
Headquarters, this is Steely. Over.

57:37.455 --> 57:39.874
She's going into Room 18.

57:46.673 --> 57:48.633
Now. Now.

58:28.173 --> 58:30.717
That's a hell of a place to park.

58:33.720 --> 58:35.597
She's checked into Room 18.
Where?

58:35.763 --> 58:37.473
Over here. Right here.

58:38.349 --> 58:39.934
Let me have that.

58:41.436 --> 58:45.565
This is the police.
You are surrounded.

58:45.773 --> 58:51.112
All right, jokers, you got 10 seconds
to come out with your hands up.

58:51.279 --> 58:52.780
Ten,

58:52.989 --> 58:54.490
nine,

58:54.699 --> 58:56.117
eight,

58:56.284 --> 58:57.410
seven...

58:59.662 --> 59:00.830
six...

59:02.457 --> 59:04.584
- She said she was 18.
- Five...

59:06.669 --> 59:11.007
four, three...
The county is really cracking down.

59:11.216 --> 59:12.467
Two,

59:12.675 --> 59:13.927
one.

59:18.514 --> 59:20.516
All right, let's go!

59:33.488 --> 59:34.489
Ah.

59:41.621 --> 59:45.667
Goddamn them. Goddamn them.
Take it easy, we'll find them.

59:45.833 --> 59:49.545
Search the entire area.
They gotta be around here
someplace.

59:49.754 --> 59:54.217
For chrissakes, how far could
they get? An all-cars alert!

59:54.425 --> 59:57.387
Sergeant Keller, I need
every man you can spare

59:57.595 --> 01:00:00.515
